\begin{abstract}
A Kakeya set is a subset of $\F^n$, where $\F$ is a finite field
of $q$ elements, that contains a line in every direction. In this
paper we show that the size of every Kakeya set is at least $C_{n}
\cdot q^{n}$, where $C_{n}$ depends only on $n$. This improves the
previously best lower bound for general $n$ of $\approx q^{4n/7}$.
\end{abstract}
